  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Casa Materna Legacy Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2000, PCI, in partnership with a local association of midwives, created the Casa Materna in the rural, western highlands of Guatemala to reduce maternal and infant mortality. Since its inception, the Casa has literally saved the lives of hundreds of mothers and their babies as well as strengthened and empowered countless Guatemalan communities.The Casa provides critically needed clinical reproductive, maternal, newborn, and child health services. Women with high-risk pregnancies are referred to the Casa inpatient facility for care and monitoring during the final weeks of their pregnancies, and are then transferred to the neighboring district hospital for delivery. In addition, the Casa supports community education and networks of women&#xD5;s support groups.</narrative>
  </description>
